<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>evaluation | Christine Bauer</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/tag/evaluation/</link><atom:link href="https://chbeu.github.io/tag/evaluation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>evaluation</description><generator>Wowchemy (https://wowchemy.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>© 2022 Christine Bauer</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 01 Dec 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://chbeu.github.io/media/sharing.png</url><title>evaluation</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/tag/evaluation/</link></image><item><title>Report on the 2nd Workshop on the Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems (PERSPECTIVES 2022) at RecSys 2022</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-sigirforum-perspectives/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 Dec 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-sigirforum-perspectives/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Proceedings of the perspectives on the evaluation of recommender systems workshop 2022</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-perspectives-ceur/</link><pubDate>Mon, 03 Oct 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-perspectives-ceur/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Second workshop: perspectives on the evaluation of recommender systems (PERSPECTIVES 2022)</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-perspectives/</link><pubDate>Thu, 22 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-perspectives/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Evaluating recommender systems: survey and framework</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-fevr/</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Aug 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2022-fevr/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Tutorial at ISMIR 2022: Trustworthy MIR: Creating MIR applications with values</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220625_ismir2022_tutorial/</link><pubDate>Sat, 25 Jun 2022 02:00:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220625_ismir2022_tutorial/</guid><description>&lt;p>I am happy to announce that I will hold a tutorial at &lt;a href="https://ismir2022.ismir.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ISMIR 2022&lt;/a> on &lt;a href="https://chbeu.github.io/talks/tu02_ismir2022_trustworthy_mir/">Trustworthy MIR: Creating MIR applications with values&lt;/a> together with &lt;a href="https://andrebola.github.io/about/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andrés Ferraro&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://emiliagomez.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Emilia Gómez&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://lorenzoporcaro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lorenzo Porcaro&lt;/a>. The goal of the tutorial is to show how values, such as fairness and diversity, can be embedded in the life cycle of MIR systems to make them trustworthy: from algorithmic design to evaluation practices and regulatory proposals. To achieve that, we will discuss examples of, among the others, popularity bias, gender bias, algorithmic bias, music styles underrepresentation, and diversity-related phenomena (e.g. filter bubbles).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Naturally, I hope that you can learn a lot from the tutorial. As a very positive side effect, I am looking forward to collaborating with &lt;a href="https://andrebola.github.io/about/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Andrés Ferraro&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://emiliagomez.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Emilia Gómez&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://lorenzoporcaro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lorenzo Porcaro&lt;/a> on this topic. For sure, we will have a blast.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Special Issue 'Perspectives on Recommender Systems Evaluation' @ TORS</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220424_si_tors/</link><pubDate>Sun, 24 Apr 2022 18:00:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220424_si_tors/</guid><description>&lt;p>Together with &lt;a href="https://evazangerle.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eva Zangerle&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://www.alansaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alan Said&lt;/a>, I am Guest Editor of the first special issue of the new journal &lt;a href="https://dl.acm.org/journal/tors/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ACM Transactions on Recommender Systems&lt;/a>: &amp;lsquo;Perspectives on Recommender Systems Evaluation&amp;rsquo;. The &lt;a href="TORS-CfP-SI-Evaluation.pdf">Call for Papers&lt;/a> and the submission details are already available. The deadline is &lt;em>&lt;strong>30 November 2022&lt;/strong>&lt;/em>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Keep in mind, that we also organize a workshop about this topic: &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PERSPECTIVES 2022&lt;/a> (which will be collocated with &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Co-Chair of PERSPECTIVES 2022</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</link><pubDate>Thu, 14 Apr 2022 17:35:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</guid><description>&lt;p>The workshop &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems&lt;/a> is back at &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>. I am happy to co-chair this workshop together with &lt;a href="https://evazangerle.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eva Zangerle&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://www.alansaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alan Said&lt;/a>. The &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/#cfp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Call for Papers&lt;/a> and the submission details are already available at the workshop website.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Report on the 1st Workshop on the Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems (PERSPECTIVES 2021) at RecSys 2021</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2021-sigirforum-perspectives/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Dec 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2021-sigirforum-perspectives/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Proceedings of the Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems Workshop 2021</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2021-perspectives-ceur/</link><pubDate>Mon, 27 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/publications/zangerle-2021-perspectives-ceur/</